1
00:01:10,319 --> 00:01:11,719
So what did you two do after that?

2
00:01:13,799 --> 00:01:15,079
After that, we went to sleep.

3
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:16,239
How exactly did you sleep?

4
00:01:16,239 --> 00:01:17,480
Do the police care about that too?

5
00:01:18,159 --> 00:01:18,959
Please don't misunderstand.

6
00:01:18,959 --> 00:01:20,239
We just want to know the details.

7
00:01:20,319 --> 00:01:21,640
It'll help your husband too.

8
00:01:23,719 --> 00:01:24,319
I'm sorry.

9
00:01:26,560 --> 00:01:27,159
Honey.

10
00:01:27,879 --> 00:01:29,519
Is something bothering you?

11
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:32,640
There's a big loan that ran into problems.

12
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:35,359
It has me completely overwhelmed.

13
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:39,680
Don't worry.

14
00:01:39,680 --> 00:01:41,439
It's fine. Don't overthink it.

15
00:01:42,519 --> 00:01:43,840
Just lie down for a bit, okay?

16
00:01:44,959 --> 00:01:46,879
Honey, you're done eating, right?

17
00:01:47,560 --> 00:01:48,879
I'll go clear the table.

18
00:01:49,359 --> 00:01:51,200
If you're not feeling well, just rest.

19
00:01:51,439 --> 00:01:52,280
I'm going to take a shower.

20
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:55,000
Oh, right.

21
00:01:56,079 --> 00:01:57,640
Just lie there and relax.

22
00:01:57,959 --> 00:01:59,040
Don't go anywhere.

23
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:07,599
Su Zhuang's alibi seems pretty solid.

24
00:02:09,520 --> 00:02:10,360
Do you believe it?

25
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:12,080
When his wife was talking,

26
00:02:12,080 --> 00:02:13,479
her behavior and expressions seemed natural.

27
00:02:13,479 --> 00:02:14,319
She didn't look like she was lying.

28
00:02:15,439 --> 00:02:16,439
Not only was she not lying,

29
00:02:16,680 --> 00:02:18,360
but every word she said was the truth.

30
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:20,479
Then Su Zhuang is cleared of suspicion.

31
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:25,599
What do you think of their marriage?

32
00:02:26,879 --> 00:02:27,960
From what I observed,

33
00:02:28,319 --> 00:02:29,319
it's probably not great.

34
00:02:29,879 --> 00:02:31,879
Su Zhuang was suddenly extra affectionate,

35
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:33,400
and she seemed a bit Flattered by it.

36
00:02:35,759 --> 00:02:37,360
But judging from her speech and manners,

37
00:02:37,439 --> 00:02:38,599
she's likely an intellectual.

38
00:02:39,080 --> 00:02:40,159
She's quite sensitive.

39
00:02:40,439 --> 00:02:41,800
Su Zhuang often doesn't come home,

40
00:02:42,520 --> 00:02:44,319
ignoring how she feels spending nights alone.

41
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:45,919
She must feel upset.

42
00:02:46,439 --> 00:02:48,479
That's why she often drowns her sorrows.

43
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:51,080
And she stressed that Su Zhuang loves her.

44
00:02:52,039 --> 00:02:53,240
Doesn't that just go to show

45
00:02:53,639 --> 00:02:55,240
she's unsure about his love,

46
00:02:55,439 --> 00:02:56,199
and afraid of losing it?

47
00:02:57,039 --> 00:02:59,240
Why did Su Zhuang suddenly change that night,

48
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:00,759
becoming so tender and considerate?

49
00:03:03,599 --> 00:03:05,120
Isn't this what they call

50
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:06,560
falling into a tender trap?

51
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:12,240
That day, she may have felt long-lost happiness.

52
00:03:14,599 --> 00:03:15,800
So Su Zhuang's odd behavior,

53
00:03:16,479 --> 00:03:17,680
she definitely didn't notice.

54
00:03:17,960 --> 00:03:19,360
But afterwards, she'd surely think it over.

55
00:03:19,680 --> 00:03:21,000
So when we were questioning her,

56
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:22,319
she was very guarded.

57
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,800
Which means she has serious doubts.

58
00:03:26,199 --> 00:03:27,840
This Su Zhuang is no simple man.

59
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:29,919
No wonder he became Bank President.

60
00:03:30,599 --> 00:03:31,240
Of course,

61
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:33,360
this is just our reasoning and speculation.

62
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:36,719
We still need evidence to back it up.

63
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:39,280
Hello?

64
00:03:43,639 --> 00:03:44,120
Okay.

65
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:45,319
I got it.

66
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:47,800
What's up, Boss?

67
00:03:48,159 --> 00:03:49,800
Shen Qing's neighbor, Zhang Yun,

68
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:52,520
listed her house for an urgent sale.

69
00:03:53,680 --> 00:03:55,479
Then this neighbor must know something.

70
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:57,840
Let's split up.

71
00:03:58,159 --> 00:04:00,319
You keep watching Su Zhuang at the bank.

72
00:04:00,319 --> 00:04:01,520
And grab some braised pork bones.

73
00:04:02,039 --> 00:04:04,039
Meet me at the park in an hour.

74
00:04:04,159 --> 00:04:04,639
Got it.

75
00:04:05,439 --> 00:04:05,879
Hey.

76
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:07,240
Braised pork bones?

77
00:04:07,960 --> 00:04:09,560
If you want some, we can go now.

78
00:04:10,159 --> 00:04:10,919
Hey, Boss.

79
00:04:11,159 --> 00:04:12,639
Why do you always leave things half-said?

80
00:04:13,039 --> 00:04:13,560
Hey.

81
00:04:16,959 --> 00:04:17,800
Ms. Zhang.

82
00:04:19,079 --> 00:04:19,800
Ms. Zhang.

83
00:04:21,480 --> 00:04:22,360
Oh, hello.

84
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:23,199
Hello, Ms. Zhang.

85
00:04:23,199 --> 00:04:24,720
I brought Mr. Li to view the house.

86
00:04:25,079 --> 00:04:25,959
Oh, please come in.

87
00:04:25,959 --> 00:04:26,800
Okay, after you.

88
00:04:28,360 --> 00:04:29,120
Feel free to look around.

89
00:04:29,959 --> 00:04:30,480
Hello.

90
00:04:30,639 --> 00:04:31,199
Hello.

91
00:04:31,519 --> 00:04:33,319
Don't touch anything in the house.

92
00:04:33,319 --> 00:04:34,839
And don't speak to the child.

93
00:04:36,839 --> 00:04:38,279
Can I see the bedrooms upstairs?

94
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:42,160
Yes, but the child's room is off-limits.

95
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:44,199
How's the soundproofing here?

96
00:04:44,759 --> 00:04:46,680
Can you hear the neighbors at night?

97
00:04:46,959 --> 00:04:48,720
It's a villa, the soundproofing's excellent.

98
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:50,600
Yes, the soundproofing is quite good.

99
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:51,439
You can't hear a thing.

100
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:53,920
Is the child's room next to the neighbor's?

101
00:04:55,240 --> 00:04:56,519
You're not really here to view the house.

102
00:04:59,199 --> 00:05:00,120
Why do you say that?

103
00:05:00,639 --> 00:05:01,959
Someone here to view the house

104
00:05:02,199 --> 00:05:03,279
walks in and asks about soundproofing,

105
00:05:03,279 --> 00:05:05,560
and then asks if the kid's room is next door.

106
00:05:06,040 --> 00:05:07,439
Doesn't that sound strange to you?

107
00:05:08,279 --> 00:05:08,959
I'm sorry.

108
00:05:09,439 --> 00:05:10,480
I was just asking.

109
00:05:11,759 --> 00:05:12,480
Suit yourself.

110
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:14,000
This way, Mr. Li. The second floor.

111
00:05:14,279 --> 00:05:15,160
Take a look around upstairs.

112
00:05:16,399 --> 00:05:17,879
Xiaoyu, Xiaoyu.

113
00:05:17,879 --> 00:05:18,839
Look at Mommy.

114
00:05:22,079 --> 00:05:23,879
Look, a puppy.

115
00:05:24,199 --> 00:05:25,399
The little puppy, Dahuang.

116
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:29,920
He loves dogs.

117
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:36,519
Hey, kid.

118
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:38,160
This dog...

119
00:05:39,279 --> 00:05:40,839
Hey, what's wrong with you?

120
00:05:41,399 --> 00:05:42,439
I told you not to touch things.

121
00:05:42,439 --> 00:05:43,480
Xiaoyu, it's okay.

122
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:44,399
Mommy's here, Mommy's here.

123
00:05:44,560 --> 00:05:45,720
No one's going to take your toys.

124
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:47,079
You.

125
00:05:47,279 --> 00:05:48,319
Take him and leave, now.

126
00:05:48,319 --> 00:05:48,839
Get out.

127
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:50,920
Get out!

128
00:05:51,639 --> 00:05:52,839
I'm sorry, I'm not a buyer.

129
00:05:52,839 --> 00:05:53,680
I'm a police officer.

130
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:56,000
I figured as much.

131
00:05:56,360 --> 00:05:56,920
Get out.

132
00:05:57,360 --> 00:05:58,319
Can I ask you a question?

133
00:06:01,560 --> 00:06:02,439
In that photo,

134
00:06:02,439 --> 00:06:03,959
the dog the child is holding is Shen Qing's, right?

135
00:06:06,399 --> 00:06:07,360
He's a stray now.

136
00:06:08,480 --> 00:06:09,759
He survives on garbage.

137
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:12,240
Every day he goes to where Shen Qing fell,

138
00:06:12,839 --> 00:06:14,079
waiting for his owner to take him home.

139
00:06:16,079 --> 00:06:16,959
His name's Pipi.

140
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:26,759
Boss.

141
00:06:27,839 --> 00:06:29,160
I got the bones for you.

142
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:30,800
I had to wait in a long line for these.

143
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:36,759
Boss.

144
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:43,040
Try some.

145
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:45,480
Did I say you could eat?

146
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:48,759
No, Boss, I bought enough for two.

147
00:06:48,759 --> 00:06:49,920
You can't finish it all yourself.

148
00:06:51,199 --> 00:06:52,680
Skipping a bite won't starve you.

149
00:06:54,079 --> 00:06:55,079
You can have the dog's leftovers.

150
00:06:55,639 --> 00:06:58,160
Boss, you're feeding such good bones to that dog?

151
00:06:58,959 --> 00:06:59,800
I need this dog.

152
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:01,319
Boss, you like dogs?

153
00:07:01,319 --> 00:07:02,279
You should've said so earlier.

154
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:05,000
If you like dogs, just buy a pet dog.

155
00:07:05,439 --> 00:07:07,079
Besides, do you even have time for a dog?

156
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:09,319
What if this dog's carrying a virus or something?

157
00:07:09,319 --> 00:07:10,480
He is a pet dog.

158
00:07:11,439 --> 00:07:12,279
His name's Pipi.

159
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:13,439
His owner just died.

160
00:07:14,759 --> 00:07:15,800
This is Shen Qing's dog?

161
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:17,279
Keep your voice down.

162
00:07:19,839 --> 00:07:22,240
No wonder he hangs around the bank every day.

163
00:07:22,879 --> 00:07:23,800
Pretty loyal.

164
00:07:23,959 --> 00:07:25,959
A real-life Hachiko, this one.

165
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:31,199
Pipi, come here.

166
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:34,319
Pipi.

167
00:07:35,759 --> 00:07:36,399
Boss.

168
00:07:36,639 --> 00:07:37,560
You're no good at this.

169
00:07:37,759 --> 00:07:38,680
Watch me, watch me.

170
00:07:38,680 --> 00:07:40,600
Don't startle him and scare him off.

171
00:07:40,639 --> 00:07:41,360
Watch this.

172
00:07:44,839 --> 00:07:45,680
Pipi, come here.

173
00:08:06,879 --> 00:08:07,399
Hey.

174
00:08:09,079 --> 00:08:10,959
Do you think I look unfriendly?

175
00:08:11,160 --> 00:08:12,120
What are you talking about, Boss?

176
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:13,879
You've got the classic good-guy face.

177
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:17,279
Then why does he ignore me when I feed him?

178
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:18,160
But he pays attention when you feed him.

179
00:08:20,040 --> 00:08:22,600
It's gotta be your overpowering aura.

180
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:24,639
Pipi's injured.

181
00:08:24,639 --> 00:08:25,600
We need to get him treated right away.

182
00:08:25,680 --> 00:08:27,120
Alright, leave him to me.

183
00:08:27,399 --> 00:08:28,199
You don't need to come along.

184
00:08:28,879 --> 00:08:29,720
You've been working hard for days.

185
00:08:29,839 --> 00:08:30,720
You should head home for a bit.

186
00:08:31,519 --> 00:08:32,159
I'm fine.

187
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:34,159
I've got a task for you.

188
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:40,360
Investigate this car's details thoroughly.

189
00:08:41,399 --> 00:08:42,120
That's it.

190
00:08:43,799 --> 00:08:44,720
Now get going.

191
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:46,279
Consider it done.

192
00:08:48,799 --> 00:08:49,639
You come with me.

193
00:08:52,480 --> 00:08:53,120
Pipi.

194
00:08:54,399 --> 00:08:55,519
See if you recognize this.

195
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:03,519
Do you know him?

196
00:09:03,879 --> 00:09:04,799
Why is it you again?

197
00:09:04,879 --> 00:09:05,360
Hello.

198
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:06,679
Pipi!

199
00:09:06,960 --> 00:09:09,440
Pipi's bleeding. He's hurt.

200
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:11,080
Thanks for bringing the dog back.

201
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:13,960
Don't mention it. These blocks are for your kid.

202
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:14,919
Thank you.

203
00:09:17,360 --> 00:09:18,200
May I come in

204
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:20,080
to put some medicine on Pipi?

205
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:21,039
I bought some medicine.

206
00:09:21,360 --> 00:09:23,000
The kid seems really worried about him.

207
00:09:25,120 --> 00:09:27,480
Xiaoyu, let's treat Pipi together, okay?

208
00:09:29,919 --> 00:09:30,600
Xiaoyu.

209
00:09:31,519 --> 00:09:32,600
Do you like building blocks?

210
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:42,080
Put this on top.

211
00:09:43,039 --> 00:09:44,480
Mister, there's a bad guy.

212
00:09:44,639 --> 00:09:46,240
A bad guy hurt Pipi.

213
00:09:47,879 --> 00:09:48,639
There, there, Xiaoyu.

214
00:09:48,759 --> 00:09:49,360
Don't be scared.

215
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:51,000
I'm a police officer.

216
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:52,360
Tell me,

217
00:09:52,879 --> 00:09:54,399
which bad guy hurt Pipi?

218
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:56,039
Hey, Xiaoyu.

219
00:09:56,320 --> 00:09:57,840
Mommy gave Pipi a bath.

220
00:09:57,840 --> 00:09:59,279
You haven't seen Pipi in a long time.

221
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:01,240
Why don't you draw a picture of him?

222
00:10:01,919 --> 00:10:03,200
Go get your notebook then.

223
00:10:12,840 --> 00:10:13,399
Here.

224
00:10:24,159 --> 00:10:24,759
Xiaoyu,

225
00:10:25,519 --> 00:10:26,440
who is this person?

226
00:10:26,679 --> 00:10:27,320
The bad guy.

227
00:11:06,919 --> 00:11:08,440
Mom, I'm home.

228
00:11:11,679 --> 00:11:12,960
What are you cooking? Smells great.

229
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:14,840
How come you're back?

230
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:15,759
Hey, let me, let me.

231
00:11:15,759 --> 00:11:16,840
Hot, hot, hot!

232
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:20,960
You brat, you haven't been home for days.

233
00:11:21,159 --> 00:11:23,200
The unit's been busy lately.

234
00:11:23,639 --> 00:11:25,519
Your dad made me worry for half my life.

235
00:11:25,519 --> 00:11:26,879
Now it's your turn.

236
00:11:28,480 --> 00:11:29,080
Mom.

237
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:32,360
Want me to crawl back into your belly?

238
00:11:32,559 --> 00:11:33,600
What kind of talk is that?

239
00:11:35,639 --> 00:11:36,159
Well?

240
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:37,080
Hungry, aren't you?

241
00:11:37,240 --> 00:11:38,519
I'm starving.

242
00:11:38,799 --> 00:11:40,360
I want your tomato and egg noodles.

243
00:11:40,360 --> 00:11:41,159
And Braised pork belly.

244
00:11:41,159 --> 00:11:43,919
Plus a Potato pancake.

245
00:11:44,039 --> 00:11:46,399
Mom knows me best.

246
00:11:47,399 --> 00:11:48,080
Hey, Mom.

247
00:11:48,840 --> 00:11:50,600
How's Dad recovering lately?

248
00:11:50,879 --> 00:11:53,039
He just got out of the hospital two days ago.

249
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:54,879
Don't upset him later.

250
00:11:55,399 --> 00:11:55,879
Okay.

251
00:11:56,600 --> 00:11:58,120
You stink. Go take a shower.

252
00:11:58,519 --> 00:11:59,399
I'll go make the pancake.

253
00:12:11,039 --> 00:12:11,679
Stop right there.

254
00:12:17,440 --> 00:12:18,120
Come here a sec.

255
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:24,639
Dad.

256
00:12:25,519 --> 00:12:26,679
Don't stand. Sit.

257
00:12:27,120 --> 00:12:28,039
I'm filthy.

258
00:12:28,320 --> 00:12:29,519
I still have to take a shower.

259
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:32,279
Work's been busy lately, huh?

260
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:34,360
Oh, yeah.

261
00:12:34,879 --> 00:12:35,799
Got a big case.

262
00:12:35,960 --> 00:12:37,159
Involves a large sum of money.

263
00:12:37,279 --> 00:12:37,919
Chief Zhang's orders.

264
00:12:37,919 --> 00:12:39,559
Forgotten what your old man did?

265
00:12:39,799 --> 00:12:41,080
Trying to fool a three-year-old?

266
00:12:42,679 --> 00:12:43,879
What are you talking about?

267
00:12:43,879 --> 00:12:45,039
Why would I fool you?

268
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:46,080
You haven't fooled me enough?

269
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:48,600
You applied to the police academy behind my back.

270
00:12:48,799 --> 00:12:50,320
Then transferred to the Detective unit behind my back.

271
00:12:50,679 --> 00:12:52,039
What else are you hiding from me?

272
00:12:54,039 --> 00:12:55,720
Dad, so you know.

273
00:12:56,879 --> 00:12:58,840
Pulling stunts while I was hospitalized.

274
00:12:59,399 --> 00:13:00,519
Think about it.

275
00:13:00,759 --> 00:13:01,799
If I hadn't given the nod,

276
00:13:01,799 --> 00:13:03,399
would Xing Junfeng dare process your transfer?

277
00:13:04,279 --> 00:13:05,360
Alright, you're good.

278
00:13:05,679 --> 00:13:06,840
I'll go take that shower now.

279
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:07,879
Come back, come back.

280
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:10,759
Dad, I'm not annoyed with you.

281
00:13:11,159 --> 00:13:12,200
I really do stink.

282
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:13,320
Mom told me to go shower.

283
00:13:14,639 --> 00:13:16,879
It's fine if you're annoyed with me.

284
00:13:17,720 --> 00:13:20,240
But never take a wrong path,

285
00:13:20,679 --> 00:13:21,840
or you'll take a bad fall.

286
00:13:22,720 --> 00:13:24,759
Dad, I'm in the Major Crimes Unit.

287
00:13:24,919 --> 00:13:26,000
I'm a Little sun.

288
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:27,440
I'm radiating light and heat.

289
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:28,559
As long as you're not a big trouble,

290
00:13:28,559 --> 00:13:29,639
I'll be at ease.

291
00:13:30,039 --> 00:13:31,559
Little sun, my foot.

292
00:13:32,279 --> 00:13:33,919
Go ask Uncle Xing.

293
00:13:34,279 --> 00:13:35,879
I got a new Boss in the unit.

294
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:36,960
This Boss is incredibly capable.

295
00:13:37,080 --> 00:13:38,559
I worked a big case with my Boss.

296
00:13:38,759 --> 00:13:39,360
A big case.

297
00:13:40,639 --> 00:13:41,519
Thank you.

298
00:13:42,120 --> 00:13:43,440
Xiaoyu's grown this big,

299
00:13:43,919 --> 00:13:46,080
and he's never interacted like this with an outsider.

300
00:13:46,360 --> 00:13:48,080
Especially after his father passed,

301
00:13:49,080 --> 00:13:50,440
he hasn't smiled since.

302
00:13:53,480 --> 00:13:54,519
You're a good mother.

303
00:13:56,159 --> 00:13:57,440
The way I treated you before,

304
00:13:57,799 --> 00:13:58,759
don't take it to heart.

305
00:13:59,039 --> 00:13:59,679
It's okay.

306
00:14:00,639 --> 00:14:03,080
I'll trust you to take care of Pipi.

307
00:14:05,120 --> 00:14:06,120
Let me ask you one more thing.

308
00:14:06,759 --> 00:14:07,559
Before this,

309
00:14:07,559 --> 00:14:09,960
why didn't you tell the police any of this?

310
00:14:10,840 --> 00:14:12,000
And even tried to sell the house?

311
00:14:28,240 --> 00:14:29,039
Don't worry.

312
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:31,320
The police will keep you safe.

313
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:33,440
I trust you.

314
00:14:33,919 --> 00:14:34,799
As for this house,

315
00:14:35,480 --> 00:14:36,320
I won't sell it anymore.

316
00:14:37,440 --> 00:14:38,559
May I ask you one more thing?

317
00:14:40,159 --> 00:14:42,919
Were you very close with Shen Qing?

318
00:14:43,960 --> 00:14:45,879
We got along well.

319
00:14:46,519 --> 00:14:48,159
We used to walk our dogs together.

320
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:50,200
She'd come over for coffee and such.

321
00:14:51,519 --> 00:14:53,279
Did she have a boyfriend?

322
00:14:55,679 --> 00:14:56,919
I wouldn't know.

323
00:14:56,919 --> 00:14:58,159
She never mentioned it to me.

324
00:14:58,720 --> 00:15:01,240
Oh, but once when Xiaoyu had a fever,

325
00:15:01,519 --> 00:15:03,039
since I don't know how to drive,

326
00:15:03,039 --> 00:15:05,840
I had her take Xiaoyu to the hospital late at night.

327
00:15:06,080 --> 00:15:07,879
When I went to her entryway,

328
00:15:09,240 --> 00:15:10,360
I remember seeing

329
00:15:10,759 --> 00:15:12,720
a man's trench coat on the rack.

330
00:15:18,840 --> 00:15:19,480
Dad.

331
00:15:20,799 --> 00:15:21,320
Dad.

332
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:23,799
Oh my.

333
00:15:23,960 --> 00:15:24,600
I know.

334
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:27,200
You've never let go of that case from twenty years ago.

335
00:15:28,519 --> 00:15:30,000
But Ma Shijiang's case,

336
00:15:30,399 --> 00:15:31,679
from what we have so far,

337
00:15:32,360 --> 00:15:34,480
has no connection to the Red Gloves case.

338
00:15:35,399 --> 00:15:36,159
I know.

339
00:15:37,360 --> 00:15:38,159
I'm fine.

340
00:15:39,759 --> 00:15:40,840
I just want to tell you,

341
00:15:41,200 --> 00:15:42,519
Being a Detective is easy,

342
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:45,679
but being a good Detective isn't.

343
00:15:47,159 --> 00:15:48,320
No matter what,

344
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:50,399
you must stay true to yourself.

345
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:53,679
Don't disgrace that Police uniform you wear.

346
00:15:53,919 --> 00:15:54,480
Got it?

347
00:15:55,679 --> 00:15:56,240
Dad,

348
00:15:57,080 --> 00:15:57,919
don't worry.

349
00:15:58,120 --> 00:15:58,799
I understand.

350
00:16:01,759 --> 00:16:02,639
I'm going to take a shower now.

351
00:16:31,759 --> 00:16:32,399
Come.

352
00:16:32,960 --> 00:16:33,679
Shake hands.

353
00:16:35,279 --> 00:16:35,919
Next.

354
00:16:37,159 --> 00:16:37,840
Shake hands.

355
00:16:41,240 --> 00:16:41,960
None of them.

356
00:16:43,039 --> 00:16:44,039
That person's hand

357
00:16:44,759 --> 00:16:45,519
was very soft.

358
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:46,799
Turn left.

359
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:51,559
Captain Jiang.

360
00:16:51,559 --> 00:16:52,200
Hand on shoulder.

361
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:53,159
Based on this alone,

362
00:16:53,399 --> 00:16:55,000
we can't confirm Red Gloves exists.

363
00:16:55,360 --> 00:16:56,879
Besides, we deployed so many officers.

364
00:16:57,159 --> 00:16:58,200
No one could've slipped through.

365
00:17:08,240 --> 00:17:10,799
How could the man entering Shen Qing's home be Lin Xiaohu?

366
00:17:10,799 --> 00:17:12,119
Nothing about this adds up.

367
00:17:13,960 --> 00:17:14,680
Chief Xing.

368
00:17:15,319 --> 00:17:16,039
Captain Li.

369
00:17:16,720 --> 00:17:18,799
Every place Lin Xiaohu might appear,

370
00:17:18,799 --> 00:17:19,720
we've searched.

371
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:21,039
No leads.

372
00:17:21,680 --> 00:17:23,359
He's likely fled Fengdu City already.

373
00:17:26,440 --> 00:17:28,119
The missing data from Shen Qing's complex,

374
00:17:28,279 --> 00:17:29,119
have you looked into it?

375
00:17:29,519 --> 00:17:30,279
We looked into it.

376
00:17:30,400 --> 00:17:31,359
Nothing suspicious turned up.

377
00:17:31,799 --> 00:17:32,680
The property manager said

378
00:17:32,680 --> 00:17:34,079
the complex's surveillance is outdated

379
00:17:34,079 --> 00:17:34,880
and breaks down often.

380
00:17:35,079 --> 00:17:36,599
Six months ago, there was already an incident

381
00:17:36,599 --> 00:17:38,079
where data went missing inexplicably.
